How to install the netAnalyzer driver:
(For further information see the Linux netAnalyzer Driver documentation.)

###############################################################################
###  Quick Start ##############################################################
###############################################################################

  1. Open a console window and enter the directory containing this README file
  2. run the installation script './build_install_driver' (root privileges
     required).
     The script will compile and install all required files (driver, library
     and firmware). To run only single installation steps see the following
     guidelines.

  3. To build the example application see step 4).

###############################################################################
###  Driver installation step by step #########################################
###############################################################################

        - Plugin the hardware and start the system               (0)
        - Build the netAnalyzer kernel module netana.ko          (1)
        - Install the firmware and the kernel module (netana.ko) (2)
        - Build the User Space library libnetana                 (3)
        - Build and run demo application                         (4)

        1)
        1.1) Enter directory ./netana_kernel_mod and run "make"

        2)
        2.1) Enter ./tools/ and run ./install_netanako install (root required)
        2.2) Run ./install_firmware install (root required)
        2.3) Run ./install_netanako update (root required)
        2.4) Run ./install_netanako load (root required)

        3)
        3.1) Enter ./libnetana/ and run "./configure"
        3.2) Run "make"
        3.3) Run "make install" (root required)

        4)
        4.1) Enter ../examples/ and run "make"
        4.3) Start application ./netana_demo (root required)